08:58.586 --> 09:01.123
not whatever this is!

09:03.332 --> 09:05.608
Here, let me show you.

09:09.416 --> 09:11.417
Grab a drink.

09:11.418 --> 09:13.898
Talk about the, uh, old days,

09:13.899 --> 09:15.970
maybe talk about the new days.

09:19.283 --> 09:20.921
Hey!

09:20.923 --> 09:23.096
Xaviers here, and he wants
to see you and me in the back,

09:23.097 --> 09:24.098
okay.

09:24.099 --> 09:26.978
Come here. Listen.

09:26.979 --> 09:29.357
Take him to my seat.
Everything is on the house.

09:29.358 --> 09:31.099
I'll be right back.

09:51.391 --> 09:54.133
You're alone.

09:54.134 --> 09:56.512
Doesn't seem right.

09:56.513 --> 09:58.993
I'm waiting for someone.

10:02.402 --> 10:05.815
I've been waiting
for someone too.

10:05.816 --> 10:07.295
I just found him.

10:07.296 --> 10:10.436
Thanks, but no thanks.

10:10.437 --> 10:13.441
Ethan told me to stop by'

10:13.442 --> 10:15.183
said he had someone
who'd like to meet me.

10:15.184 --> 10:17.824
Hey! I see you two have met.

10:17.825 --> 10:19.532
You get rid of her'?

10:19.533 --> 10:20.910
Ease up.

10:20.911 --> 10:23.357
Wound that tight,
you'll give yourself a stroke.

10:23.358 --> 10:24.701
I'm not interested

10:24.702 --> 10:29.048
in whatever it is
you're selling.

10:29.049 --> 10:30.585
Yeah?

10:30.586 --> 10:31.929
Well, you can go fuck yourself,

10:31.930 --> 10:35.605
because I'm definitely
not gonna.

10:35.606 --> 10:38.780
You still owe me that gram.

10:41.040 --> 10:44.453
That was something.

10:44.454 --> 10:46.127
I'm leaving.

10:47.947 --> 10:49.654
Look, foley,
I'll take you home,

10:49.655 --> 10:51.657
but could you just give me
one minute?

10:51.658 --> 10:54.332
Just hang back a second.

10:59.893 --> 11:01.998
This is what we like to see,

11:01.999 --> 11:05.572
empty bottles
means business is good.

11:05.573 --> 11:07.814
A veuve, dom, cristal..

11:07.815 --> 11:10.318
Very nice, but, uh...

11:10.319 --> 11:12.595
Oh! What have we here?

11:12.596 --> 11:15.839
The '96 billecart-salmon.

11:15.840 --> 11:17.547
It's a shame to open this'

11:18.687 --> 11:20.928
Really, it needs
another 10 or 15 years.

11:20.929 --> 11:23.307
But if you're some
hedge fund shithead

11:23.308 --> 11:26.551
trying to pry into the pants
of some poor, unfortunate girl,

11:26.552 --> 11:30.728
well, you need to do
what you need to do.

11:33.904 --> 11:36.077
I had the '59 a few weeks ago.

11:36.078 --> 11:37.853
It was absolutely spectacular.

11:37.854 --> 11:43.964
The minerality weaves
the elements together like silk.

11:43.965 --> 11:46.275
I love champagne,

11:46.276 --> 11:49.280
I drink a lot of it because
I have a lot to celebrate.

11:49.281 --> 11:54.287
Life is good
when my people do their jobs.

11:54.288 --> 11:59.397
This happened on your watch,
Ethan.

11:59.398 --> 12:01.139
It won't happen again.

12:01.140 --> 12:04.144
Xavier, I'm the one that
caught the stupid motherfucker.

12:04.145 --> 12:05.932
And that's why, one day,
if you're a good boy,

12:05.982 --> 12:10.041
I'll let you try the-the '59.

12:10.091 --> 12:13.947
Our colleague here
won't have that opportunity,

12:13.997 --> 12:16.614
so you thought, what,
that I wouldn't notice?

12:16.664 --> 12:20.217
$250.000!

12:20.267 --> 12:21.385
And I wouldn't notice?

12:35.655 --> 12:39.404
Gonna be kind of tough
to get the money back now.

12:39.454 --> 12:42.235
You'll find a way.

12:43.997 --> 12:47.144
Have a safe flight.

12:49.497 --> 12:50.715
Deal with it.

12:50.765 --> 12:52.484
Foley. Foley.

12:52.534 --> 12:55.486
Just... Give me a
minute, please.

12:55.536 --> 12:57.924
I got out of prison yesterday.
Yesterday!

12:57.974 --> 12:58.945
I know.

12:58.946 --> 13:00.591
I know, and I'm sorry for that,

13:00.641 --> 13:02.427
but just listen to me.

13:02.477 --> 13:05.764
I thought that we would go out,
you know'?

13:05.814 --> 13:07.667
Have a drink.

13:07.717 --> 13:12.966
I guess I was just trying to
show you that I'm like my dad.

13:15.295 --> 13:19.775
But the truth is,

13:19.825 --> 13:23.582
I never really knew the guy,

13:23.632 --> 13:24.849
you know, my mom, she was...

13:24.899 --> 13:27.044
What do you want from me,
Ethan?

13:29.942 --> 13:32.889
I want to know
why you killed my father.

13:50.830 --> 13:54.979
Still a lot of money
to be made down there.

13:55.029 --> 13:58.649
Just how much do you know
about me and your dad?

13:58.699 --> 14:01.818
Only what my mom told me,

14:01.868 --> 14:06.122
that you were best
friends, partners.

14:06.172 --> 14:08.494
She tell you what we did?
Our work'?

14:08.544 --> 14:10.515
. No.

14:10.516 --> 14:12.655
But I figured it out.

14:22.161 --> 14:24.577
It's everything I could find.

14:24.627 --> 14:28.346
Every article, every picture.

14:28.396 --> 14:29.845
Why would you keep all this?

14:29.895 --> 14:31.515
How else
could I get to know him?

14:31.565 --> 14:33.352
You were grifters,

14:33.402 --> 14:37.219
best in the city, according
to a lot of the old-timers.

14:58.898 --> 15:02.749
Ethan, you need to let this go.

15:02.799 --> 15:04.583
Your dad's been dead
a long time.

15:04.633 --> 15:06.885
No, I need to know.

15:06.935 --> 15:09.443
Foley,
put yourself in my shoes.

15:19.285 --> 15:21.201
We were on the grift...

15:21.251 --> 15:24.435
A long con with a volatile mark

15:24.485 --> 15:28.105
but with a high yield
if it played.

15:28.155 --> 15:31.241
And it played.

15:31.291 --> 15:32.578
Till your dad got greedy

15:32.628 --> 15:35.279
and tried to squeeze the mark
loo hard,

15:35.329 --> 15:37.914
I never figured out why.

15:37.964 --> 15:40.049
He was in debt.

15:40.099 --> 15:44.253
He was way over his
head, cards, horses.

15:44.303 --> 15:46.957
Took my mom years
to get out from under it.

15:47.007 --> 15:48.981
I'm sorry to hear that.

15:51.417 --> 15:53.299
Mark was a heavy hitter.

15:53.349 --> 15:56.298
Didn't take well
to being ripped off.

15:56.348 --> 16:02.328
Kill your dad, or I
could die with him.

16:15.136 --> 16:18.958
I'm sorry.

16:30.289 --> 16:33.639
I spent a long time
in a very small room

16:33.689 --> 16:36.475
thinking about
the choices I made that night.

16:36.525 --> 16:39.965
I was young,
younger than you are now,

16:39.966 --> 16:42.146
but I made a choice.

16:42.196 --> 16:44.713
I never broke frame,

16:44.763 --> 16:46.739
and I was punished for it.

16:49.175 --> 16:51.321
What was his name?

16:51.371 --> 16:53.389
The mark'

16:53.439 --> 16:55.413
what's it matter?

16:55.414 --> 16:56.694
He was the mark.

16:56.744 --> 16:58.165
Your dad put us both
in a corner,

16:58.215 --> 17:00.499
and there was only one way out.

17:00.549 --> 17:02.334
Well, if somebody
did that to me,

17:02.384 --> 17:06.172
I'd kill him too.

17:06.222 --> 17:07.865
I'm just saying...

17:10.363 --> 17:11.406
I understand.

17:11.457 --> 17:12.541
You understand?

17:12.592 --> 17:13.643
Yeah, I do,

17:13.693 --> 17:16.178
and I think we can help
each other.

17:16.228 --> 17:18.652
Look at me, Ethan.

17:18.702 --> 17:22.088
25 years of my life are gone.

17:22.137 --> 17:24.388
Now, if you're as smart
as you think you are,

17:24.439 --> 17:26.089
you should go in this room,

17:26.140 --> 17:28.325
rip that shit down
off that wall,

17:28.375 --> 17:30.994
and throw it away!

18:52.798 --> 18:54.112
This isn't the kind of thing

18:54.162 --> 18:55.677
where we got to make small talk,
is it'?

18:55.727 --> 18:57.203
Can I just watch my game?

19:09.649 --> 19:11.030
Pitcher of your cheapest.

19:11.080 --> 19:12.465
Sit anywhere you like.

19:12.515 --> 19:14.834
You think'?

19:14.884 --> 19:17.366
Oh, shit.

19:17.416 --> 19:19.131
Watch it.

19:43.249 --> 19:45.395
I said no. Get off me.

19:45.445 --> 19:47.733
Got to go to the bathroom-
shit.

19:50.017 --> 19:52.304
Oh. Damn.

19:52.354 --> 19:54.600
Always choke in the clutch.

20:37.403 --> 20:40.286
' No!

20:40.336 --> 20:42.307
Leave it be.

20:42.308 --> 20:44.811
He's bad business'

20:46.412 --> 20:48.226
No, no.

20:48.276 --> 20:49.392
Please stop.

20:49.442 --> 20:50.414
Shut up.

20:50.415 --> 20:51.561
Please stop.

20:51.611 --> 20:53.033
She said stop.

20:53.083 --> 20:55.097
Get the fuck out of here!

20:55.147 --> 20:57.431
After you.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.082
Hey. Hey.
He can't hurt you now.

21:10.132 --> 21:12.952
Put it down. Put it down.

21:17.937 --> 21:20.225
God damn.

21:28.483 --> 21:30.634
It's-it's all right.

21:30.684 --> 21:33.938
It's okay. Hey.

21:33.988 --> 21:36.461
How you know this guy?

21:36.462 --> 21:37.843
I just met him tonight.

21:37.893 --> 21:41.612
He was supposed
to go get me some...

21:41.662 --> 21:44.449
Hey, you're that freak
from the other night.

21:50.643 --> 21:53.025
Beautiful.

21:59.185 --> 22:00.999
For your trouble.

22:01.049 --> 22:03.369
What about your cut'?

22:03.419 --> 22:04.703
I wasn't even here.

22:04.753 --> 22:09.507
What about the girl?
She's waiting inside.

22:09.557 --> 22:11.208
Tell her I said good night,

22:33.419 --> 22:35.065
Good to go.

22:37.216 --> 22:38.190
Oh, the pipes!

22:40.785 --> 22:42.761
Hey!

22:44.196 --> 22:45.341
What the hell happened?

22:45.391 --> 22:46.745
I could have been
fucking killed!

22:46.795 --> 22:48.180
Ll don't know.
It was all secure.

22:48.230 --> 22:49.244
I don't give a shit!

22:49.294 --> 22:50.683
You come to work
looking like hell!

22:50.733 --> 22:51.704
You almost killed my guy!

22:51.705 --> 22:53.749
Now, get off my site! Now!

22:53.799 --> 22:55.187
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

22:55.237 --> 22:56.521
Brother man, hey, look.

22:56.571 --> 22:57.754
I need this job.

22:57.804 --> 22:59.388
Look, I will make it
worth your while.

22:59.438 --> 23:01.091
I will kick back double
what you asked'

23:01.141 --> 23:03.354
this shit could never be
worth my while.

23:19.365 --> 23:22.471
Hey, at least new
you have time for coffee.

23:24.870 --> 23:26.381
Ethan, did you have
anything to do

23:26.431 --> 23:27.854
with what happened back there?

23:27.904 --> 23:29.119
Of course not.

23:29.169 --> 23:30.787
'Cause I need this job
for my parole.

23:30.837 --> 23:32.022
I have to make money.

23:32.072 --> 23:36.558
Oh, you have needs? Tell me.

23:36.608 --> 23:40.399
What do you need?

23:40.449 --> 23:41.919
I thought I made myself clear.

23:41.920 --> 23:43.370
Oh, yeah, that's right.

23:43.420 --> 23:45.771
You're going straight.

23:45.821 --> 23:49.761
The same thing
every con says at first.

23:49.762 --> 23:51.610
But you're not every con.

23:51.660 --> 23:54.080
You've got skills,
skills I can use.

23:54.130 --> 23:56.602
What are you talking about'?

23:59.438 --> 24:02.450
I'm putting together a grift

24:02.500 --> 24:03.552
and not just any grift.

24:03.602 --> 24:06.290
I've got the perfect mark

24:06.340 --> 24:09.729
for the samaritan.

24:09.779 --> 24:11.928
That's what I'm talking about.

24:11.978 --> 24:15.267
That's why I need you on board.

24:15.317 --> 24:20.906
That's your grift,
you and my dad.

24:20.956 --> 24:25.744
I'm not your dad, Ethan,
and I don'! Want to be.

24:31.136 --> 24:37.314
You know, my mom was alone
for a long time.

24:39.345 --> 24:44.793
But when I'm 17,
she brings home this new guy,

24:44.843 --> 24:48.296
and he takes us out to dinner,

24:48.346 --> 24:49.966
orders me a steak,

24:50.016 --> 24:54.002
so I know that he sees me
as a man, not a boy,

24:54.052 --> 24:58.372
and they tell me
they're getting married.

25:00.699 --> 25:03.048
What am I supposed to say
to that'?

25:03.098 --> 25:06.317
Well, sure, I'd love a dad
who owns a shitty body shop

25:06.367 --> 25:08.619
and smells of urinal cakes.

25:08.669 --> 25:15.160
So I eat my steak,
and I go to work.

25:15.210 --> 25:16.325
Late night calls

25:16.375 --> 25:18.061
to the same number
on his cell bill.

25:18.111 --> 25:23.503
Motel room charges
on his credit card.

25:23.553 --> 25:26.067
Of course, I don'! Say a word.

25:26.117 --> 25:28.873
Let mom figure it out.

25:28.923 --> 25:31.676
And when she does,
I'm on his side.

25:31.726 --> 25:35.846
"Give him another shot,"
which she does.

25:35.896 --> 25:38.515
Until I pay a pro to show up

25:38.565 --> 25:40.250
saying he owes her 200 bucks

25:40.300 --> 25:43.155
for the abortion
he made her have.

25:45.141 --> 25:47.189
The poor bastard.

25:47.239 --> 25:50.095
He had no idea what hit him.

25:50.145 --> 25:52.728
But I knew”.

25:52.778 --> 25:57.221
I was my father's son.

25:57.222 --> 26:01.438
Sc, yeah, you're right.

26:01.488 --> 26:04.675
You're not my father.

26:04.725 --> 26:08.277
But I don't need a father.

26:08.327 --> 26:12.516
I need a partner.

26:12.566 --> 26:14.386
Your mom ever find
anybody else?

26:14.436 --> 26:16.586
What'? No.

26:16.636 --> 26:19.248
Sorry to hear that.

26:20.879 --> 26:22.924
You have no idea
what I can do for you.

26:24.177 --> 26:29.622
Ethan, stay away from me.

26:37.996 --> 26:40.744
Any fallout
from the other night?

26:40.794 --> 26:44.412
